about.summary: Faker is a Python package that generates fake data for you.

name: fake-factory
raw_recipe:
{%set name = "fake-factory" %}
{%set version = "0.5.8" %}
{%set hash_type = "sha256" %}
{%set hash_val = "d004b53e9e5340c0879eb59941d6e0edae3a0a840c28b5cc84fd66b2732b218f" %}

package:
  name: {{ name }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: {{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  {{ hash_type }}: {{ hash_val }}

build:
  entry_points:
    - faker=faker.cli:execute_from_command_line

  number: 0
  script: python setup.py install --single-version-externally-managed --record=record.txt

requirements:
  build:
    - python
    - setuptools
    - python-dateutil >=2.4
    - six
    - importlib  # [py26]
    - ipaddress  # [py26 or py27]

  run:
    - python
    - python-dateutil >=2.4
    - six
    - importlib  # [py26]
    - ipaddress  # [py26 or py27]
